
[1]fulminate

   FUL'MINATE, v.i. [L. fulmino, from fulmen, thunder, from a root in Bl,
   which signifies to throw or to burst forth.]

   1. To thunder.

   2. To make a loud sudden noise, or a sudden sharp crack; to detonate;
   as fulminating gold.

   3. To hurl papal thunder; to issue forth ecclesiastical censures, as
   the pope.

                              FUL'MINATE, v.t.

   1. To utter or send out, as a denunciation or censure; to send out, as
   a menace or censure by ecclesiastical authority.

   2. To cause to explode.
